  🧠 Philosophical Resolution

  The Meta-Reference Paradox: A tool that enforces patterns must reference those patterns to detect them.

  Solution: Exclusion (not suppression) is the correct approach:
  - Meta-tools operate at a different logical level than production code
  - Analogous to compilers not type-checking themselves
  - Consistent with Gödel's incompleteness (can't fully validate from within)

  Why Not Suppress?
  - Clutters code with self-referential comments
  - Doesn't scale (every new rule needs suppressions)
  - Maintenance burden

